<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1138,1844]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
The species herein included in the group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valladares et al." authorityYear="2002" box="[640,720,1139,1164]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[640,720,1139,1164]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have commonly been recognized as members of the controversial genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1907" box="[312,465,1179,1204]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Phrynosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,465,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Phrynosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Werner" box="[480,637,1178,1204]" firstAuthor="Werner" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="147 - 155" refId="ref74444" refString="Werner, F. (1907) In: Burger, O. (Ed.), Estudios sobre reptiles chilenos. Anales Universidad de Chile, 121, 147 - 155." type="journal article" year="1907">Werner 1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Donoso-Barros" box="[649,909,1178,1204]" firstAuthor="Donoso-Barros" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref57808" refString="Donoso-Barros, R. (1966 a) Reptiles de Chile. Ediciones de la Universidad de Chile, Santiago, 458 pp." type="book" year="1966" yearSuffix="a">Donoso-Barros 1966a</bibRefCitation>
, b, 
<bibRefCitation author="Donoso-Barros, R." box="[951,1013,1178,1204]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="129 - 134" refId="ref58174" refString="Donoso-Barros, R. (1972) Contribucion al conocimiento del genero Ctenoblepharis Tschudi y Phrynosaura Werner (Sauria, Iguanidae). Boletin Sociedad de Biologia de Concepcion, 44, 129 - 134." type="journal article" year="1972">1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez &amp; Jaksic" box="[1025,1281,1178,1204]" firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="63 - 91" refId="ref67479" refString="Nunez, H. &amp; Jaksic, F. M. (1992) Lista comentada de los reptiles terrestres de Chile continental. Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 43, 63 - 91." type="journal article" year="1992">Núñez &amp; Jaksic 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="67 - 88" refId="ref67598" refString="Nunez, H., Navarro, J., Garin, C., Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; V. Meriggio, D. (2003) Phrynosaura manueli y Phrynosaura torresi, nuevas especies de lagartijas para el norte de Chile (Squamata: Sauria). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 52, 67 - 88." type="journal article" year="2003">
Núñez 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Over the last century, many authors have suggested that clear patterns of differentiation in osteological and cytogenetical traits observed exclusively in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etheridge" authorityYear="1995" baseAuthorityName="Nunez &amp; Yanez" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[715,904,1259,1284]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="audituvelatus">
<emphasis box="[715,904,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. audituvelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1068,1259,1284]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="erroneous">
<emphasis box="[919,1068,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. erroneous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1083,1208,1259,1284]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="manueli">
<emphasis box="[1083,1208,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. manueli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valladares" authorityYear="2004" box="[1223,1428,1259,1284]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poconchilensis">
<emphasis box="[1223,1428,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. poconchilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valladares et al." authorityYear="2002" box="[151,262,1299,1324]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[151,262,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nunez, Navarro, Garin, Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Meriggio" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[320,428,1299,1324]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torresi">
<emphasis box="[320,428,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">L. torresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would support the hypothesis that these species represent a discrete evolutionary line (
<emphasis box="[161,202,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez" box="[211,422,1338,1364]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="11 - 14" refId="ref67716" refString="Nunez, H., Navarro, J., Sufan, J. &amp; Galaz, J. L. (1998) Distribucion geografica de Phrynosaura (Reptilia, Tropiduridae). Noticiario Mensual Museo Nacional de Historia Natural, 334, 11 - 14." type="journal article" year="1998">
Núñez 
<emphasis box="[295,354,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez, H. &amp; Navarro, J. &amp; Garin, C. &amp; Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Meriggio, D." box="[435,498,1338,1364]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="67 - 88" refId="ref67598" refString="Nunez, H., Navarro, J., Garin, C., Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; V. Meriggio, D. (2003) Phrynosaura manueli y Phrynosaura torresi, nuevas especies de lagartijas para el norte de Chile (Squamata: Sauria). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 52, 67 - 88." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
). Yet, on the other hand, some studies conclude that these traits may not be sufficient evidence to separate this still hypothetical group of species from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[1112,1234,1379,1404]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1234,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Liolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Frost &amp; Etheridge" firstAuthor="Frost" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref59836" refString="Frost, D. R. &amp; Etheridge, R. (1989) A phylogenetic analysis and taxonomy of iguanian lizards (Reptilia: Squamata). University of Kansas Museum Natural History, Miscellaneous Publications, 81, 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1989">Frost &amp; Etheridge 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge" box="[350,536,1418,1444]" firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref59230" refString="Etheridge, R. (1995) Redescription of Ctenoblepharys adspersa Tschudi, 1845, and the taxonomy of Liolaeminae (Reptilia: Squamata: Tropiduridae). American Museum Novitates, 3142, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1995">Etheridge 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge &amp; Espinoza" box="[550,884,1418,1444]" firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref59521" refString="Etheridge, R &amp; Espinoza, R. E. (2000) Taxonomy of the Liolaeminae (Squamata: Iguania: Tropiduridae) and a semiannotated bibliography. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 126, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2000">Etheridge &amp; Espinoza 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Valladares" box="[898,1092,1418,1444]" firstAuthor="Valladares" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="41 - 51" refId="ref73450" refString="Valladares, J. P. (2004) Nueva especie de lagarto del genero Liolaemus (Reptilia: Liolaemidae) del norte de Chile, previamente confundido con Liolaemus (= Phrynosaura) reichei. Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 18, 41 - 51." type="journal article" year="2004">Valladares 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Recent molecular phylogenies have contributed to clarify in part this problem. This research reveals that at least the two “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1907" box="[1270,1423,1459,1484]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Phrynosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1270,1423,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Phrynosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species analysed phylogenetically so far, are nested within 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[859,981,1499,1524]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[859,981,1499,1524]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Liolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Valladares" box="[998,1264,1498,1524]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Valladares" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="473 - 489" refId="ref73496" refString="Valladares, J. P., Etheridge, R., Schulte II, J. A., Manriquez, G. &amp; Spotorno, A. (2002). Nueva especie de lagartija del norte de Chile, Liolaemus molinai (Reptilia: Liolaeminae). Revista Chilena de Historia Natural, 75, 473 - 489." type="journal article" year="2002">
Valladares 
<emphasis box="[1132,1192,1499,1524]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schulte" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Schulte" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="408 - 420" refId="ref71740" refString="Schulte II, J. A., Losos, J. B., Cruz, F. B. &amp; Nunez, H. (2004) The relationship between morphology, escape behaviour and microhabitat occupation in the lizard clade Liolaemus (Iguanidae: Tropidurinae: Liolaemini). Journal of Evolutionary Biology, 17, 408 - 420." type="journal article" year="2004">
Schulte 
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,1499,1524]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, these findings appear to support 
<bibRefCitation author="Frost &amp; Etheridge's" box="[766,1091,1538,1564]" firstAuthor="Frost" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref59836" refString="Frost, D. R. &amp; Etheridge, R. (1989) A phylogenetic analysis and taxonomy of iguanian lizards (Reptilia: Squamata). University of Kansas Museum Natural History, Miscellaneous Publications, 81, 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1989">Frost &amp; Etheridge’s (1989)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge's" box="[1155,1377,1538,1564]" firstAuthor="Etheridge's" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref59230" refString="Etheridge, R. (1995) Redescription of Ctenoblepharys adspersa Tschudi, 1845, and the taxonomy of Liolaeminae (Reptilia: Squamata: Tropiduridae). American Museum Novitates, 3142, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1995">Etheridge’s (1995)</bibRefCitation>
proposal that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1907" box="[272,425,1579,1604]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Phrynosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,425,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Phrynosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" authorityYear="2005" box="[746,868,1579,1604]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[746,868,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Liolaemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, it still remains unknown whether the currently six species assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Werner" authorityYear="1907" box="[577,730,1619,1644]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Phrynosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[577,730,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Phrynosaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(or alternatively to the group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valladares et al." authorityYear="2002" box="[1080,1160,1619,1644]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[1080,1160,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez" box="[1220,1431,1618,1644]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="67 - 88" refId="ref67598" refString="Nunez, H., Navarro, J., Garin, C., Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; V. Meriggio, D. (2003) Phrynosaura manueli y Phrynosaura torresi, nuevas especies de lagartijas para el norte de Chile (Squamata: Sauria). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 52, 67 - 88." type="journal article" year="2003">
Núñez 
<emphasis box="[1304,1362,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Valladares" box="[151,343,1658,1684]" firstAuthor="Valladares" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="41 - 51" refId="ref73450" refString="Valladares, J. P. (2004) Nueva especie de lagarto del genero Liolaemus (Reptilia: Liolaemidae) del norte de Chile, previamente confundido con Liolaemus (= Phrynosaura) reichei. Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 18, 41 - 51." type="journal article" year="2004">Valladares 2004</bibRefCitation>
) actually form a monophyletic clade within this genus (phylogenetic evidence suggest that these species are members of the series 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pincheira-Donoso" authorityYear="2005" box="[620,709,1699,1724]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signifer">
<emphasis box="[620,709,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see above). Since the anatomical and cytogenetical evidence reported in previous papers suggests that these six species would be closely related taxa (
<bibRefCitation author="Nunez" box="[1206,1422,1738,1764]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nunez" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="67 - 88" refId="ref67598" refString="Nunez, H., Navarro, J., Garin, C., Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; V. Meriggio, D. (2003) Phrynosaura manueli y Phrynosaura torresi, nuevas especies de lagartijas para el norte de Chile (Squamata: Sauria). Boletin del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 52, 67 - 88." type="journal article" year="2003">
Núñez 
<emphasis box="[1292,1352,1739,1764]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
), we include them into the group 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valladares et al." authorityYear="2002" box="[550,630,1779,1804]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="reichei">
<emphasis box="[550,630,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">reichei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[652,694,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">e.g.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Valladares" box="[706,903,1778,1804]" firstAuthor="Valladares" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="41 - 51" refId="ref73450" refString="Valladares, J. P. (2004) Nueva especie de lagarto del genero Liolaemus (Reptilia: Liolaemidae) del norte de Chile, previamente confundido con Liolaemus (= Phrynosaura) reichei. Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 18, 41 - 51." type="journal article" year="2004">Valladares 2004</bibRefCitation>
). However, further phylogenetic studies are needed to test the validity of this classification criterion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
